Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all
produce. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Toss on a
#baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp}, @garlic powder{1%tsp},
@salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until
browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, slice @Roma Tomato{1} into ½-inch-thick rounds. Halve
@Brioche Buns{2}. In a #small bowl{}, combine @Blue Cheese Dressing{3%ounce}
and @Sour Cream{4%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Season tomato slices all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of
@olive oil{1%tsp} in a large, preferably nonstick, #pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add tomato and cook until lightly browned and slightly softened,
~{2-3%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

While tomato cooks, form @Ground Beef{10%ounce} into two patties (four patties
for 4 servings), each a bit wider than a burger bun. Season generously with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in pan used for tomato over medium-high heat.
Add patties and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. In the last
~{1-2%minutes} of cooking, top each patty with @Monterey Jack Cheese{1/4%cup};
cover pan until cheese melts.

Toast buns. Spread insides of top buns with half the blue cheese sauce. Fill
buns with patties, griddled tomato, and @Crispy Fried Onions{1}. Serve with
potato wedges and remaining blue cheese sauce on the side.